[48;5;237m[38;5;231m---CONNECTIVITY SPEC---[39m                                                         [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m# v1 Connectivity Spec — `@relay-assistant/connectivity`[39m                        [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m**Status:** IMPLEMENTATION_READY[39m                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m**Date:** 2026-04-11[39m                                                            [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m**Package:** `@relay-assistant/connectivity`[39m                                    [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m**Version target:** v0.1.0 (pre-1.0, provisional)[39m                               [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m**Canonical scope:** `docs/architecture/v1-connectivity-scope.md` [39m              [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m(SCOPE_LOCKED)[39m                                                                  [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m---[39m                                                                             [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m## 1. Responsibilities[39m                                                          [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m`@relay-assistant/connectivity` provides a typed, in-process signaling layer [39m   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mfor internal multi-agent coordination. It is not a generic event bus or pub/sub[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m system. It is the mechanism by which specialists, coordinators, and supporting[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m subsystems communicate state, confidence, handoffs, conflicts, and escalations[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m without verbose transcript exchange.[39m                                           [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m**Owns:**[39m                                                                       [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- `ConnectivitySignal` — the canonical signal envelope and all supporting types[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Signal emission — assigning IDs, timestamps, and initial state[39m                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Signal state machine — `emitted → active → [superseded | expired | resolved]`[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Signal log — in-memory, per-thread, queryable log of all signals[39m              [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Suppression — step-basis or time-basis duplicate detection[39m                    [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Audience resolution — translating semantic audience (`self`, `coordinator`, [39m  [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m`selected`, `all`) to recipient identifiers[39m                                     [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Routing escalation hook — one-directional interface to routing on escalation [39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231memit[39m                                                                            [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Signal salience — defined per signal class; used by suppression and [39m          [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mconvergence logic[39m                                                               [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m**Does NOT own:**[39m                                                               [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Model invocations or reasoning[39m                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Routing mode selection or model spec (→ `@relay-assistant/routing`)[39m           [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Coordinator/specialist orchest[39m                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m… +1473 lines …[39m                                                                 [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mwnership, no coordination ownership, no transport implementation[39m                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m5. specify the minimum tests to write now[39m                                       [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mEnd the document with V1_CONNECTIVITY_PACKAGE_IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN_READY.[39m        [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m---[39m                                                                             [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mSTEP OWNER CONTRACT:[39m                                                            [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- You are the accountable owner for step "lead-connectivity-plan".[39m              [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- If you delegate, you must still verify completion yourself.[39m                   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Preferred final decision format:[39m                                              [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  OWNER_DECISION: <one of COMPLETE, INCOMPLETE_RETRY, INCOMPLETE_FAIL, [39m         [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mNEEDS_CLARIFICATION>[39m                                                            [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  REASON: <one sentence>[39m                                                        [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Legacy completion marker still supported: [39m                                    [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mSTEP_COMPLETE:lead-connectivity-plan[39m                                            [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Then self-terminate immediately with /exit.[39m                                   [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m---[39m                                                                             [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mAUTONOMOUS DELEGATION — READ THIS BEFORE STARTING:[39m                              [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mYou have approximately 60 minutes before this step times out. Plan accordingly [39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m— delegate early if the work is substantial.[39m                                    [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mBefore diving in, assess whether this task is too large or complex for a single[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m agent. If it involves multiple independent subtasks, touches many files, or [39m   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mcould take a long time, you should break it down and delegate to helper agents [39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mto avoid timeouts.[39m                                                              [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mOption 1 — Spawn relay agents (for real parallel coding work):[39m                  [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  - mcp__relaycast__agent_add(name="helper-1", cli="claude", task="Specific [39m    [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231msubtask description")[39m                                                           [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  - Coordinate via mcp__relaycast__message_dm_send(to="helper-1", text="...")[39m   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  - Check on them with mcp__relaycast__message_inbox_check()[39m                    [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  - Clean up when done: mcp__relaycast__agent_remove(name="helper-1")[39m           [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mOption 2 — Use built-in sub-agents (Task tool) for research or scoped work:[39m     [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  - Good for exploring code, reading files, or making targeted changes[39m          [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  - Can run multiple sub-agents in parallel[39m                                     [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mGuidelines:[39m                                                                     [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- You are the lead — delegate but stay in control, track progress, integrate [39m   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mresults[39m                                                                         [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Give each helper a clear, self-contained task with enough context to work [39m    [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mindependently[39m                                                                   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- For simple or quick work, just do it yourself — don't over-delegate[39m           [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Always release spawned relay agents when their work is complete[39m               [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- When spawning non-claude agents (codex, gemini, etc.), prepend to their task:[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m  "RELAY SETUP: First call register(name='<exact-agent-name>') before any other[39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m relay tool."[39m                                                                   [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m---[39m                                                                             [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mIMPORTANT: When you have fully completed this task, you MUST self-terminate by [39m [49m
